+
+Okay, so I've been asked to address these TypeScript errors 
+in src/index.ts. It seems the core issue revolves around    
+assigning a type object | undefined to a variable declared  
+as type object in the merged field of MergeResult.  The     
+errors are popping up on lines 221 and 239.                 
+
+Looking at the context, line 221 is assigning theirs to     
+merged[docId].  theirs is derived from                      
+this.versions.get(theirsVerId)!.content, and crucially, this
+seems to be where the issue originates.  The logic suggests 
+that if theirsVerId exists (which the code checks), then    
+theirs should be an object. The non-null assertion ! is     
+there, but TypeScript isn't smart enough to connect the     
+dots.                                                       
+
+On line 239, we have merged[docId] = ours || theirs;. Both  
+ours and theirs can be undefined, so ours || theirs can also
+be undefined. However, the prompt specifies that merged     
+should contain the merge result (with conflicts resolved in 
+favor of 'ours' for the purpose of showing what it would    
+look like).  The key here is understanding the scenarios: If
+a document is deleted on both sides or deleted on one side  
+but unchanged on the other side and we favor the delete, the
+document should no longer be in the merged record. The      
+merged field should only contain documents that exist in the
